==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pedigree clause
<hw>Ped"i*gree clause</hw>. <def>A clause sometimes inserted in
contracts or specifications, requiring that a material of construction,
as cement, must be of a brand that has stood the test of a specified
number of years' use in an important public work.</def> <mark>[Cant, U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pediluvy</ent>⟦br⟧
